democratize information and to make information

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:48.230
available to people that it didn't used to
be so they now have opportunities that didn't

00:00:48.230 --> 00:00:49.800
used to be possible.

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:54.210
At the Boys and Girls Club, our vision is
for all of our youth to grow up to become

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:55.610
self sufficient adults.

00:00:55.610 --> 00:01:00.660
Now there's a challenge there because today,
right here in the heart of Silicon Valley,

00:01:00.660 --> 00:01:04.869
just four miles from where we're sitting,
over half the kids are dropping out of high

00:01:04.869 --> 00:01:08.390
school and that's the challenge that we face
at the Boys and Girls Clubs, that's the problem

00:01:08.390 --> 00:01:10.760
that we're addressing, that we're trying to
solve.

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:16.440
We do that through two ways, the first step
we have is to bring our members in to track

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:20.440
the youth and provide them a sense of belonging
and to give them a place where they can be

00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:24.780
safe, have relationships with adults and really
get a sense that someone cares about them

00:01:24.780 --> 00:01:26.340
and they belong.

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:30.700
The second thing we do is we help instill
in them, help them develop, the academic and

00:01:30.700 --> 00:01:33.350
life skills they need to thrive.

00:01:33.350 --> 00:01:37.840
So I thought what we'd do today is share with
you some of the stories of some of our amazing

00:01:37.840 --> 00:01:41.960
members so you can hear from them directly
how growing up in circumstances that are very

00:01:41.960 --> 00:01:48.200
challenging, they've persevered, they thrived
and they've really developed the skills required

00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:51.650
to be successful and are amazing, amazing
young men and women.

